OL,3,CWill extra powers help London shed the
OL,4,Ctitle of Britain's fly-tipping capital?
OL,6,FCouncils will be given greater powers
OL,7,Fto tackle fly-tipping as several
OL,8,FLondon boroughs make the list for
OL,9,Fbeing the worst in Britain.
OL,11,FPeople caught transporting and dealing
OL,12,Fwith waste illegally could face five
OL,13,Fyears in jail or have their vehicles
OL,14,Fseized and crushed.
OL,16,FCouncils will receive no extra cash
OL,17,Ffor the plan and are expected to use
OL,18,Ffunding from their budget.
